"{\"uid\": \"fortune.com-europe-2024-03-19-52-french-restaurants-earn-their-first-michelin-stars-summer-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"As France prepares to welcome the world for\\u00a0the summerOlympicsin Paris, the nation\\u00a0has dozens of shiny, newly starred restaurants to show off-62 to be exact.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 157, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3, \"end\": 9, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.899137401593663e-44, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 65, \"end\": 70, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.752269237518511e-54, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The number of three-starred dining rooms, the zenith of fine\\u00a0dining, in the nation increased to 30;last year it was 29.\", \"from\": 159, \"to\": 278, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Two years ago,31 restaurants heldthat\\u00a0top number.\", \"from\": 279, \"to\": 328, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the newly minted three stars is\\u00a0Le Gabriel at La Reserve Paris near the\\u00a0Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es.\", \"from\": 330, \"to\": 424, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 394, \"end\": 399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.752269237518511e-54, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 409, \"end\": 423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"score\": 0.9938637728108773, \"rank\": 0.005341849563966386, \"text\": \"Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chef J\\u00e9r\\u00f4me Banctel specializes in dishes with influences from around the world, like\\u00a0lobster cooked on Japanese binchotan charcoal with\\u00a0almond pralines.\", \"from\": 425, \"to\": 578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 529, \"end\": 537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_cuisine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.019791377938974e-23, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_cuisine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_cuisine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The other new three-star spot is La Table du Castellet in Le Castellet in southern France, where chef Fabien Ferr\\u00e9 runs the kitchen.\", \"from\": 580, \"to\": 712, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 613, \"end\": 621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Table\", \"score\": 0.999999091522526, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"La Table\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Table\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_Table\"}, {\"begin\": 625, \"end\": 634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Castellet-en-Luberon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Castellet\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Castellet-en-Luberon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Castellet-en-Luberon\"}, {\"begin\": 638, \"end\": 650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Circuit_Paul_Ricard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4265057853799272e-27, \"text\": \"Le Castellet\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Circuit_Paul_Ricard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Circuit_Paul_Ricard\"}, {\"begin\": 663, \"end\": 669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.899137401593663e-44, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 689, \"end\": 694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9o_Ferr\\u00e9\", \"score\": 0.4740022591739337, \"rank\": 0.7741935483869542, \"text\": \"Ferr\\u00e9\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9o_Ferr\\u00e9\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9o_Ferr\\u00e9\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am not so good at speeches, I am better in the kitchen,\\\" he said at the awards ceremony, surrounded by the other three-star chefs.\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 846, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At 35 years old, he's the youngest in the category.\", \"from\": 847, \"to\": 898, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His inspired cooking features on menus such as \\\"Expression Marine\\\"\\u00a0which might include a dish like mackerel with aloe vera, celery and kiwi.\", \"from\": 899, \"to\": 1039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1012, \"end\": 1021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aloe_vera\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"aloe vera\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aloe_vera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aloe_vera\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ferr\\u00e9 took over the restaurant from mentor Christophe Bacqui\\u00e9, who earned three stars for the establishment in 2018.\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1157, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1041, \"end\": 1046, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9o_Ferr\\u00e9\", \"score\": 0.4740022591739337, \"rank\": 0.7741935483869542, \"text\": \"Ferr\\u00e9\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9o_Ferr\\u00e9\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9o_Ferr\\u00e9\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The restaurant closed in 2022,\\u00a0and Ferr\\u00e9 reopened the dining room in 2023.\", \"from\": 1158, \"to\": 1232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1193, \"end\": 1198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9o_Ferr\\u00e9\", \"score\": 0.4740022591739337, \"rank\": 0.7741935483869542, \"text\": \"Ferr\\u00e9\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9o_Ferr\\u00e9\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9o_Ferr\\u00e9\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In so swiftly earning the top ranking, the young chef has pulled off a notable feat.\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1317, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The stars were announced\\u00a0on Monday,\\u00a0March 18 at a live event in Tours, a city on the lower reaches of the Loire River in central France that's famous for its creamy pork spread,\\u00a0rillettes.\", \"from\": 1319, \"to\": 1507, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1448, \"end\": 1454, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.899137401593663e-44, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France is the home of theMichelinguide and the country with the world's most Michelin stars.\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1509, \"end\": 1515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.899137401593663e-44, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1586, \"end\": 1594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.856324741841855e-100, \"text\": \"Michelin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This year was marked by an increasing focus on regions outside of the French capital, according to Gwendal Poullennec, international director of Guide Michelin, who spoke at the introduction of the event.\", \"from\": 1602, \"to\": 1806, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1672, \"end\": 1678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.213087248678293e-14, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1747, \"end\": 1761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Guide Michelin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even as the guide has been expanding to cities and regions all over the world, like Colorado and Atlanta, \\\"France has a special position [for the Guide],\\\"\\u00a0Poullennec said.\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 1978, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1891, \"end\": 1899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado\", \"score\": 0.9999808151409025, \"rank\": 1.741196224819154e-05, \"text\": \"Colorado\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colorado\"}, {\"begin\": 1904, \"end\": 1911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3842285468408522e-15, \"text\": \"Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\"}, {\"begin\": 1914, \"end\": 1920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.899137401593663e-44, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony, and the run on new starred dining rooms,\\u00a0came as economies have slowed worldwide and consumers are still struggling with higher living costs.\", \"from\": 1980, \"to\": 2135, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In an interview with Bloomberg, Ferr\\u00e9\\u00a0said he has witnessed first-hand the importance of earning three Michelin stars for the hotel-restaurant's business.\", \"from\": 2137, \"to\": 2291, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2158, \"end\": 2167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bloomberg_News\", \"score\": 0.8986863214746312, \"rank\": 0.11185478429682302, \"text\": \"Bloomberg\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bloomberg_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bloomberg_News\"}, {\"begin\": 2169, \"end\": 2174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9o_Ferr\\u00e9\", \"score\": 0.4740022591739337, \"rank\": 0.7741935483869542, \"text\": \"Ferr\\u00e9\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9o_Ferr\\u00e9\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/L\\u00e9o_Ferr\\u00e9\"}, {\"begin\": 2240, \"end\": 2248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.856324741841855e-100, \"text\": \"Michelin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"From one day to the next the phone started ringing off the hook,\\\"\\u00a0he said.\", \"from\": 2292, \"to\": 2367, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As of now, he says, they still have availability for the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2368, \"to\": 2434, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But who knows.\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2450, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe in a couple of days that might not be the case.\\\"\", \"from\": 2451, \"to\": 2505, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This year there are 8 new two-star restaurants, a notable number that's double last year's\\u00a0count.\", \"from\": 2507, \"to\": 2604, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Among them is one of France's most famous spot, Le Jules Verne on the second\\u00a0floor of the\\u00a0Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 2605, \"to\": 2708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2626, \"end\": 2632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.899137401593663e-44, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2656, \"end\": 2667, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eiffel_Tower\", \"score\": 0.9999998993680543, \"rank\": 1.0063214195928693e-07, \"text\": \"Jules Verne\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eiffel_Tower\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eiffel_Tower\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another new two-star eatery is Les Grandes Alpes in Courchevel: On stage, chef Sylvestre Wahid described his journey\\u00a0from arriving\\u00a0in France as a child from Pakistan without speaking French to now having two Michelin stars.\", \"from\": 2709, \"to\": 2932, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2843, \"end\": 2849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.899137401593663e-44, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2866, \"end\": 2874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"score\": 0.9999991408207333, \"rank\": 8.500224507162014e-07, \"text\": \"Pakistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\"}, {\"begin\": 2892, \"end\": 2898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.213087248678293e-14, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2917, \"end\": 2925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.856324741841855e-100, \"text\": \"Michelin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This year there are 52 new\\u00a0one-star restaurants in the country.\", \"from\": 2934, \"to\": 2997, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of them is\\u00a0Le Tout-Paris in the Cheval Blanc hotel, which features a modern brasserie menu with dishes like blue lobster in a bergamot infused sauce.\", \"from\": 2998, \"to\": 3151, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3013, \"end\": 3026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tout-Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Le Tout-Paris\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tout-Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tout-Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another new one star is Espadon Restaurant at the Ritz Paris, headed up by its first female chef, Eug\\u00e9nie B\\u00e9ziat.\", \"from\": 3152, \"to\": 3265, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3176, \"end\": 3183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_submarine_Espadon_(S637)\", \"score\": 0.9999999896581357, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Espadon\", \"types\": [\"Q11446\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_submarine_Espadon_(S637)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_submarine_Espadon_(S637)\"}, {\"begin\": 3250, \"end\": 3257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eug\\u00e9nie_de_Montijo\", \"score\": 0.9943613620269766, \"rank\": 0.002218934911241232, \"text\": \"Eug\\u00e9nie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eug\\u00e9nie_de_Montijo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eug\\u00e9nie_de_Montijo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I follow my inspiration, it's who I am,\\\" she said, accepting her award.\", \"from\": 3266, \"to\": 3338, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(It's not the first time\\u00a0B\\u00e9ziat has headed up a one-star kitchen; previously she had one at\\u00a0La Flibuste in Villeneuve-Loubet.)\", \"from\": 3339, \"to\": 3465, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3446, \"end\": 3463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Villeneuve-Loubet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Villeneuve-Loubet\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Villeneuve-Loubet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Villeneuve-Loubet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Outside Paris, new one stars included\\u00a0Alpage in the resort town of Courchevel in the Alps.\", \"from\": 3467, \"to\": 3557, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3475, \"end\": 3480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.752269237518511e-54, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ahead of this year's announcement, the Michelin guide announced bad news for some restaurants.\", \"from\": 3559, \"to\": 3653, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3598, \"end\": 3606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.856324741841855e-100, \"text\": \"Michelin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The publication downgraded Ren\\u00e9 et Maxime Meilleur from three stars to two;\\u00a0the restaurant is run by the eponymous\\u00a0father-and-son team in\\u00a0the Savoie region.\", \"from\": 3654, \"to\": 3810, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3796, \"end\": 3802, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Savoie\", \"score\": 0.9999995904628051, \"rank\": 4.0953697161536904e-07, \"text\": \"Savoie\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Savoie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Savoie\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"