nce\": \"Twenty-six establishments lost their one-star status.\", \"from\": 4205, \"to\": 4258, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When Paris hosts\\u00a0the Olympics this summer, the country's gastronomic heritage\\u00a0will be highlighted.\", \"from\": 4260, \"to\": 4358, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4265, \"end\": 4270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.752269237518511e-54, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alain Ducasse, whose French-based restaurant empire has the most Michelin stars of any on earth, will\\u00a0prepare a dinner for about 100 visiting heads of state.\", \"from\": 4359, \"to\": 4516, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4359, \"end\": 4372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alain_Ducasse\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2942953557991205e-80, \"text\": \"Alain Ducasse\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alain_Ducasse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alain_Ducasse\"}, {\"begin\": 4424, \"end\": 4432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.856324741841855e-100, \"text\": \"Michelin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The meal is scheduled for\\u00a0July 25, the day before the opening ceremony, to be served under the Louvre Pyramid.\", \"from\": 4517, \"to\": 4627, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Among the special awards given out were eight to pastry chefs, for a\\u00a0category called \\\"Passion Desserts.\\\"\", \"from\": 4629, \"to\": 4733, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of\\u00a0the winners was\\u00a0Aurora Storari from Hemicycle in Paris; her specialties include\\u00a0roasted Jerusalem artichoke souffl\\u00e9.\", \"from\